---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Find Your Own Answers - Be More Free">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative py-24 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-50 via-white to-accent-50"></div>
    
    <!-- Decorative elements -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-96 h-96 bg-gradient-to-bl from-accent-200/20 to-transparent rounded-full blur-3xl"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-96 h-96 bg-gradient-to-tr from-primary-200/20 to-transparent rounded-full blur-3xl"></div>
    
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <div class="text-6xl mb-6">üß≠</div>
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8 leading-tight">
          Find Your Own <span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-primary-600 to-accent-500">Answers</span>
        </h1>
        <p class="text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          No advice, no frameworks, no predetermined paths. Your wisdom emerges with space.
        </p>
        <nav class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700 transition-colors">
          <a href="/booking/free-trial" class="inline-flex items-center">
            ‚Üê Back 
          </a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <!-- Core Principle -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
          You Already Know More Than You Think
        </h2>
        
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-50 to-accent-50 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-8">
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Most therapeutic and coaching approaches assume you need someone else's expertise 
            to understand your own life. They offer advice, strategies, frameworks, and solutions 
            based on their training and experience.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            The Neutral Zone operates from a different premise: you have more wisdom about 
            your own experience than anyone else could possibly have. When given genuine space 
            to look, your own answers emerge naturally. You already have everything you need, Neutral Zone allows you to see that more clearly.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What You Usually Get -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">
          What You Usually Get Instead
        </h3>
        
        <div class="grid gap-6">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-red-50 to-orange-50 border border-red-200 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 text-red-900 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-red-500 mr-3 text-2xl">‚úó</span>
              External Solutions
            </h4>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
              <li>"Have you tried this technique?"</li>
              <li>"Here's what I recommend you do..."</li>
              <li>"Based on research, the best approach is..."</li>
              <li>"Let me give you some strategies that work"</li>
              <li>"Other clients have found success with..."</li>
              <li>"You should consider..."</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What Finding Your Own Answers Looks Like -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">
          What Finding Your Own Answers Looks Like
        </h3>
        
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-green-900">
              Example: "I don't know what to do about my job"
            </h4>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-red-700 mb-2">Typical Response:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  "Let's do a pros and cons list," or "Have you considered talking 
                  to HR?" or "Maybe you need better boundaries..."
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700 mb-2">Neutral Zone Response:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  "What's there when you look at staying? What's there when 
                  you look at leaving?"
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-green-900">
              Example: "I keep sabotaging my relationships"
            </h4>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-red-700 mb-2">Typical Response:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  "Let's explore your attachment style," or "This might be about 
                  your fear of intimacy. Here are some exercises..."
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700 mb-2">Neutral Zone Response:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  "What happens inside you right before you sabotage? 
                  What's that like?"
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
            <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4 text-green-900">
              Example: "I'm always anxious about everything"
            </h4>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-red-700 mb-2">Typical Response:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  "Let's try some breathing exercises," or "Anxiety often comes 
                  from catastrophic thinking. Let's work on that..."
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700 mb-2">Neutral Zone Response:</p>
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic">
                  "What does the anxiety feel like? Is there any message or flow to you from that feeling? 
                  What do you need to look at around that 'anxious about everything'?"
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Why Your Answers Are Better -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">
          Why Your Answers Are Better
        </h3>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:border-primary-300 transition-colors">
            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
              <span class="text-3xl">üéØ</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">They're Specific to You</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  Your answers emerge from your actual experience, not from general 
                  principles or what works for other people.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:border-primary-300 transition-colors">
            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
              <span class="text-3xl">üí™</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">They Come with Built-in Motivation</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  When you discover something yourself, you don't need to be convinced 
                  of it or motivated to act on it‚Äîthe understanding itself creates movement.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:border-primary-300 transition-colors">
            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
              <span class="text-3xl">üå±</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">They Lead to Real Understanding</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  External advice might give you something to try, but your own insights 
                  give you clarity and choice that changes how you see and respond to things.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-white border-2 border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6 hover:border-primary-300 transition-colors">
            <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
              <span class="text-3xl">üîí</span>
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">They Don't Create Dependence</h4>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  When you find your own answers, you don't become dependent on someone 
                  else for guidance. You develop trust in your own capacity to understand.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- How This Works -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">
          How Your Answers Emerge
        </h3>
        
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-50 to-orange-50 border-2 border-amber-300 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            In a truly neutral space, when you're not being guided or directed, something 
            remarkable happens: you naturally begin to explore what's actually there. 
            Without someone else's agenda influencing your looking, you can see things 
            you might never have noticed.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Your own wisdom doesn't need to be taught or activated‚Äîit just needs space 
            to emerge. When you're given that space, insights often arise spontaneously. 
            You start to understand the actual dynamics of your situation rather than 
            applying someone else's theory to it.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            The facilitator's role is simply to maintain that neutral space and support 
            your own looking, without adding their material or steering you toward 
            predetermined conclusions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What If You Don't Find Answers -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">
          "What If I Don't Find Answers?"
        </h3>
        
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-2 border-blue-300 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Sometimes the most valuable discovery is that you don't have an answer yet‚Äîand 
            that's perfectly fine. Knowing that you don't know something is its own form 
            of clarity and can be more honest than accepting someone else's answer.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Other times, the "answer" isn't a solution to implement, but simply understanding 
            what's actually happening. Understanding your patterns, recognizing your responses, 
            seeing what's really there‚Äîthese insights often create change by themselves.
          </p>
          
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            The goal isn't to leave every session with an action plan. The goal is to see 
            clearly, and from that clarity, your own choices emerge naturally.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Principles -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8 text-center text-gray-900">
        Other Neutral Zone Principles
      </h3>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/principles/no-altitude" class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all group">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">üéØ</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">No One Has Altitude Over You</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">You explore what YOU want to explore</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
        
        <a href="/principles/truth" class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all group">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">üíØ</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">Everything You Say is Truth</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Your experience is valid, period</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
        
        <a href="/principles/hours-not-years" class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all group">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">‚ö°</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">Hours, Not Years</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Address what's actually there</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
        
        <a href="/principles/complete-acceptance" class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all group">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">ü§ù</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">Complete Acceptance</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Examine all parts without judgment</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
        
        <a href="/principles/no-prerequisites" class="bg-white rounded-xl p-4 border border-gray-200 hover:border-primary-300 hover:shadow-lg transition-all group">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
            <span class="text-2xl">üöÄ</span>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold group-hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors">No Prerequisites</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Just start looking</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-24 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-primary-600 via-primary-700 to-accent-600"></div>
    
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center relative z-10">
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-6">
        Discover Your Own Wisdom
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-white/90 mb-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Your first 30-minute Neutral Zone session is free. Experience what happens 
        when you have space to find your own answers.
      </p>
      <a href="/booking/free-trial" 
         class="group bg-white text-primary-700 px-12 py-6 rounded-full text-xl font-bold hover:bg-accent-400 hover:text-white transition-all duration-300 transform hover:scale-105 shadow-2xl inline-flex items-center">
        Book Your Free Trial Session
        <span class="ml-3 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-transform">‚Üí</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
